This folder contains circuit diagram developed in Proteus 8.11 as well as results displaying different level of fuel in a tank.
When the tank is empty the LED will display "EMPTY" and the motor starts.
When the tank is 1/4th filled the LED will display "1/4 FULL" and motor remains in its state.
When the tank is half filled the LED will display "HALF" and motor remains in its state.
When the tank is 3/4th filled the LED will display "3/4 FULL" and motor remains in its state.
When the tank is completely filled the LED will display "FULL" and motor stops.
The motor remains stop until the tank becomes empty and meanwhile the LED displays the corresponding water level.